FLUPS Licensing
============================================

This file includes all licenses that apply within FLUPS (this program) source tree, in particular any that are supposed to be exposed to the end user for credit requirements for instance. 

FLUPS is a Fourier-based Library of Unbounded Poisson Solvers.

Copyright (C) <2020, 2022> <Universite catholique de Louvain (UCLouvain), Belgique>


The contributors to the development of FLUPS are given by alphabetical order:

- v1.0 (2020, under Apache 2.0 license)::
    - Denis-Gabriel Caprace
    - Thomas Gillis

    note: the authors particularly thank Dr. Jonathan Lambrecht and Prof. Philippe Chatelain for helpfull discussions.

- v2.0 (2022, under BSD-3 license):
    - Pierre Balty
    - Thomas Gillis

note: all authors are or were affiliate to the Universite catholique de Louvain, UCLouvain, when they developed FLUPS


Website:
    https://github.com/vortexlab_uclouvain/flups


Contact:
    Thomas Gillis           thomas.gillis@uclouvain.be
    Denis-Gabriel Caprace   denis-gabriel.caprace@uclouvain.be
    Pierre Balty            pierre.balty@uclouvain.be

